.DT
query_flow
Disk World creator help
query_flow

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
query_flow -  This function returns the strength of the current flowing through a particular exit, if any.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
int query_flow(string dir)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^dir%^RESET%^ - the exit which should have its current returned
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
the current through this ext.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/room/basic/water.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This function returns the strength of the current flowing through a
particular exit, if any.  A positive value represents a current flowing from
this room into the next one, and a negative value represents a current
flowing from the next room into this one.
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
add_flow, delete_flow, query_flows

.EP

